data.content:
Works. Here's the summary of the two APIs (both on `JsonSerializerOptions`):

| Goal | Method | Returns |
|---|---|---|
| Typed metadata | `GetTypeInfo<T>()` | `JsonTypeInfo<T>` directly — no cast |
| Probe without throwing | `TryGetTypeInfo<T>(out JsonTypeInfo<T>?)` | `bool` — `false` if unavailable |

The key lines:

```csharp
// Strongly-typed — throws if unavailable
JsonTypeInfo<Person> info = options.GetTypeInfo<Person>();

// Probe — returns false instead of throwing
if (options.TryGetTypeInfo<Order>(out JsonTypeInfo<Order>? info))
    // use info
```

Both are generic overloads that give you back `JsonTypeInfo<T>` so you never need to cast from the non-generic `JsonTypeInfo`.
